parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission, specifically in second gear, can cause the motorcycle to slip out of gear, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential rider injury.
symptoms: The transmission slips out of gear
especially in second gear
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the motorcycle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents and potential rider injury.
symptoms: The clutch chatters or vibrates
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake rotor can cause vibration, rattling, and screeching noises, leading to a safety hazard, especially during emergency braking.
symptoms: The rear brake rotor is loose
rattles over bumps
screeches when brakes are applied
has excessive movement
and may cause the clutch to malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel leak can cause a fire hazard, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Fuel smell or fumes
fuel leaking from under the gas tank
fuel leaking down the front cylinder
intermittent fuel leaks
